			<h3 ><a href="#p161583">Re: you know how...?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=161583&amp;sid=e5d828c4e121f6a9e5fff5f994528e0c#p161583"><img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/styles/tjp-embed/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9433&amp;sid=e5d828c4e121f6a9e5fff5f994528e0c" style="color: #43C6DB;" class="username-coloured">phreadom</a></strong> &raquo; Sun 12.06.2009 1:28 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I'm not saying it couldn't be used that way. I think it has a lot to do with the tone of how actually say the sentence.<br /><br />&quot;You know you lent me your camera.. ? Well... I broke it by accident...&quot; would probably sound fine if the tone matched the other way of saying it.<br /><br />I just wouldn't expect to hear it said that way... I would hear it as a reminder, not a lead in to a further explanation like the other way of saying it. It would make sense once they continued on with the explanation... but initially I would think they were reminding me for the sake of reminding me, not because they wanted to establish that fact before moving on to a further explanation.</div>

			<div id="sig161583" class="signature">猿も木から落ちる</div>

