			<h3 ><a href="#p161593">Re: you know how...?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=161593&amp;sid=e5d828c4e121f6a9e5fff5f994528e0c#p161593"><img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/styles/tjp-embed/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17039&amp;sid=e5d828c4e121f6a9e5fff5f994528e0c" style="color: #00AA00;" class="username-coloured">Yudan Taiteki</a></strong> &raquo; Sun 12.06.2009 8:49 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I did want to point out that at least for me, &quot;you know how...&quot; doesn't have to lead to a negative conclusion, just an unexpected one.<br /><br />&quot;You know how I thought that article was going to be really difficult?  Actually I finished it in one day.&quot;</div>

			<div id="sig161593" class="signature">-Chris Kern</div>

